   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO NOURISHING AND CARING FOR THE NEW BELIEVERS Scripture Reading: John 21:15; 15:16; 1 Thes 2:7; Rom 9:5; 1 Tim 2:5; Luke 2:11; 1 Cor 15:45b; John 4:24; Rom 10:12; 1 Pet 2:2; Rom 12:1; Acts 5:42 OUTLINE Feeding the Lord's lambs John 21:15: That our fruit may remain John 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>As a nursing mother cherishing her own children 1 Thes 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Leading the new believers: To know the Lord: As God Rom 9:5.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>As man 1 Tim 2:5.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>As the Savior including the Redeemer Luke 2:11.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>As the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To know that they have a regenerated spirit for worshipping God the Lord John 4:24.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To call on the name of the Lord, to pray to Him, and to take in His riches Rom 10:12.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Leading them to grow in life that they may present themselves to God as living sacrifices 1 Pet 2:2; Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Needing to meet with the new believers in their homes in order to feed them Acts 5:42: This being the pattern revealed in the New Testament.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>This being also the second step needed for the New Testament believers to minister as priests of the gospel.</S>
   </TEXT>
